<br>
If your friends level past you, you will find new friends in your group range. With the advent of the chat channels, it's a bit easier to find groups now than it was when I started here. The language barrier really halted alot of chances at making good friends and grouping in a diverse area. <br>
<br>
I say go for it. FV is a great place to live. The mobs are more frequent, less camping, less KS (though it is still there) and overall a less crowded environment. <br>
<br>
As for young players, anyone level 20 or over is probably here to stay. Up to that point, you find people giving up their characters and moving on to other blue servers or even PvP. Its a bit tougher to level, get groups etc..<br>
<br>
Don't let the difficulties turn you back. <br>
<br>
